{
  "red_failure_evidence": "Before the work the verify failed twice over: 'No such file or directory' on references/merge-prompt.md in BOTH skill roots, and 'missing D3' because SKILL.md cited no merge decisions at all. control-loop.sh also still carried its explicit guard refusing --role merge as not implemented, so the merge half of the cockpit could not start even in principle. Exit 1.",
  "green_evidence": "MERGE_ROLE_WIRED / rc=0, re-run independently by the orchestrator after my own fix. The verify ends by running one real loop iteration with --role merge against a stubbed claude on PATH, so it proves the guard is gone and the merge prompt resolves and is passed.",
  "orchestrator_review": "The worker preserved the no-retry rule where it was asked to, but the delivered text contained a contradiction I caught on review: it said the red worktree is not re-attempted 'this iteration' while also saying 'a later iteration will find it still finished and eligible'. Those cannot both hold. Sixty seconds later a fresh cold process would have tried the same merge again, and again - and with the PBI-039 flake at one red in twelve, a flaky verify would have gone green within about twelve minutes and merged the very thing the red result was protecting main from. Retrying once a minute is still retrying. Fixed: before attempting any merge the role reads the chat pane's scrollback for an existing MERGE_VERIFY_RED line naming that slug and skips it silently if present - the same no-state-file mechanism D18 already forces on anomaly de-duplication, with the human's acknowledgement being the act of clearing the report."
}
